        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 5. Halecium beanii (Johnston, 1838). (A, D) From Roscoff; (B, C, E–H) from The Faroes. (A–C) Colony silhouettes (scale bar: 1 cm); (D–F) subterminal portions of branches (scale bar: 0.2 mm); (G) female gonotheca, middle one seen from side of hydrothecae, right one shown with developing embryos (scale bar: 0.2 mm); (H) male gonotheca (same scale bar as G)." ;
